or this special case, which\nserves as a motivation for that general theorem, whose proof involves much more\nintricate arguments. We remark that any continuous stationary process verifies\nthe property that almost all realizations belong to an ergodic algebra, and\nthat $\\APs(\\R^d)$ is, so far, the greatest known ergodic algebra on $\\R^d$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 30 Apr 2014 21:32:20 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 4 Oct 2014 14:56:47 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 23 Oct 2014 08:25:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-10-24"}
